nd%20cooled%20was%20astonishing%20and%20impressive.%20Thanks%20to%20its%20use%20of%20efficient%20induction%2C%20it%20was%20ready%20to%20go%20with%20the%20touch%20of%20two%20buttons%20and%20mere%20seconds%20of%20preheating.%20You%20can%20set%20the%20digital%20temperature%20control%20to%20various%20levels%20that%20go%20up%20to%20a%20blazing%20575%20F%3B%20significantly%20higher%20than%20any%20other%20electric%20wok%20we've%20tested.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20a%20digital%20timer%2C%20but%20this%20isn't%20the%20type%20of%20appliance%20you'll%20want%20to%20walk%20away%20from.%20This%20carbon%20steel%20wok%20gets%20hot%20fast%2C%20and%20food%20will%20scorch%20and%20smoke%20faster%20than%20you%20think.%20The%20induction%20technology%20relies%20on%20a%20magnetic%20connection%20between%20the%20pot%20and%20the%20base%3A%20all%20the%20heat%20goes%20right%20into%20the%20pot%2C%20while%20the%20surrounding%20area%20stays%20cool%20to%20the%20touch.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESurprisingly%2C%20this%20electric%20wok%20set%20was%20able%20to%20impart%20%3Cem%3Ewok%20hei%3C%2Fem%3E%20without%20a%20single%20lick%20of%20flame.%20Meats%20seared%20stunningly%2C%20vegetables%20blistered%2C%20charred%2C%20and%20popped%20with%20abandon%2C%20rice%20crackled%20and%20crisped%2C%20sauce%20reduced%20rapidly%20and%20gained%20luscious%20viscosity%2C%20and%20every%20single%20ingredient%20became%20infused%20with%20a%20hint%20of%20smoke%20without%20becoming%20burnt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20performance%20of%20this%20electric%20wok%20is%20flawless%3B%20never%20have%20I%20ever%20experienced%20such%20authentic%2C%20restaurant-quality%20results%20at%20home.%20As%20for%20my%20personal%20feelings%20of%20connectedness%20to%20the%20cookware%2C%20the%20strong%20wave%20of%20familiarity%20that%20washed%20over%20me%20as%20my%20brain%20connected%20to%20my%20memories%20of%20cooking%20at%20my%20parents'%20Chinese%20takeout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWhat%20to%20look%20for%20in%20the%20best%20woks%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFlat%20versus%20round%20bottoms%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Flat-bottomed%20woks%20are%20better%20suited%20for%20home%20use%20because%20round-bottomed%20woks%20require%20a%20wok%20ring%2C%20a%20metal%20band%20that%20holds%20the%20cookware%20in%20place%20on%20a%20gas%20stove%20burner%20and%20directs%20the%20heat%20to%20and%20around%20the%20wok.%20This%20workaround%20is%20really%20only%20suited%20for%20gas%20stoves%2C%20as%20they%20can%20slide%20off%20electric%20and%20glass-top%20burners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlat-bottomed%20woks%20are%20the%20most%20common%20consumer-available%20designs%2C%20but%20their%20dimensions%20vary%20tremendously%2C%20which%20is%20part%20of%20why%20product%20tests%20like%20this%20are%20necessary.%20All%20the%20best%20woks%20used%20for%20this%20guide%20were%20flat-bottomed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaterial%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0Carbon%20steel%20is%20a%20traditional%20favorite%20for%20making%20woks%2C%20while%20cast%20iron%20and%20stainless%20steel%20are%20great%20for%20casual%20cooks.%20Here%20are%20the%20strengths%20and%20weaknesses%20of%20each%20material%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ECarbon%20steel%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20is%20traditionally%20a%20favorite%20material%20for%20woks%20because%20it%20reacts%20quickly%20to%20heat%20adjustments%20and%20has%20a%20natural%20nonstick%20surface%20once%20seasoned.%20But%20be%20warned%3A%20it%20takes%20a%20lot%20of%20heavy%2C%20repeated%20usage%20to%20get%20to%20this%20level%2C%20which%20is%20why%20it's%20not%20recommended%20for%20the%20casual%20home%20cook%2C%20and%20why%20we%20did%20not%20include%20any%20carbon%20steel%20woks%20in%20this%20test.%20We%20are%20looking%20forward%20to%20testing%20some%20pre-seasoned%20carbon%20steel%20woks%20for%20the%20next%20update%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ECast%20iron%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20is%20a%20bit%20more%20accessible%20as%20people%20are%20more%20accustomed%20to%20maintaining%20it%2C%20but%20it's%20important%20to%20bear%20in%20mind%20that%20it's%20a%20very%20heavy%20material%20and%20will%20limit%20your%20maneuverability.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EStainless%20steel%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20has%20been%20growing%20in%20Western%20popularity%20since%20it's%20durable%20and%20not%20prone%20to%20rust.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EAluminum%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20woks%20are%20lighter%20and%20hotter%20but%20prone%20to%20warp%20and%20ding.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EHard%20anodized%20and%20nonstick%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20pans%20provide%20greater%20ease%20of%20use%20in%20a%20familiar%20medium%2C%20but%20their%20performance%20will%20vary%20based%20on%20manufacturer-determined%20specs%2C%20like%20thickness%20and%20finish.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHandles%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20There%20are%20two%20main%20types%20of%20handles%20on%20the%20best%20woks%3A%20loop%20and%20stick.%20%3Cstrong%3EA%20loop-handled%2C%20or%20Canton%20wok%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20is%20meant%20for%20tumble%20cooking%2C%20which%20means%20using%20a%20scoop%20and%20spatula%20to%20quickly%20agitate%20ingredients%20(like%20fried%20rice)%20and%20spark%20faster%20liquid%20evaporation%20and%20spot%20charring.%20Loop%20handled%20woks%20are%20also%20great%20for%20pan-frying%2C%20which%20requires%20constant%20contact%20with%20the%20heat%20source%3B%20steaming%3B%20and%20big%20batch%20cooking%2C%20as%20they%20traditionally%20tend%20to%20be%20wider%20than%20long-handled%20woks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELong-handled%20or%20stick-handled%20woks%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20are%20meant%20for%20toss%20cooking%2C%20such%20as%20with%20saucy%20dishes%20and%20stir-fries%20that%20incorporate%20larger-cut%20ingredients.%20In%20this%20technique%2C%20you%20lift%20the%20wok%20off%20the%20burner%20and%20toss%20the%20ingredients%20into%20the%20air%20using%20a%20shake%20of%20your%20wrist.%20Traditional%20long-handled%20woks%20offer%20a%20deeper%20basin%20in%20the%20middle%20for%20thickening%20sauces%20and%20higher%20walls%2C%20and%20are%20lightweight%20for%20maneuverability%20in%20order%20to%20flip%20and%20toss%20off%20the%20burner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHow%20we%20tested%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Fried%20rice%20sits%20inside%20a%20wok%20as%20part%20of%20testing.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F60bfb2c42feb6f00181ed9ca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFor%20all%20of%20our%20wok%20tests%2C%20we%20used%20the%20same%20high-powered%20burner%20of%20a%20gas%20stove.%3Cp%3ESu-Jit%20Lin%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20tested%2016%20of%20the%20best%20woks%20of%20various%20materials%2C%20looking%20at%20construction%20quality%20and%20scratch%20resistance%3B%20heat%20retention%20and%20distribution%3B%20ease%20of%20cleaning%20and%20handling%3B%20and%20overall%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20each%20wok%2C%20I%20made%20two%20dishes%20chosen%20for%20the%20multiple%20Asian%20cooking%20techniques%20they%20required%2C%20and%20utilized%20high%20smoke-point%2C%20neutral%20avocado%20oil%20to%20provide%20a%20cleaner%20background%20for%20any%20sign%20of%3Cem%3E%20wok%20hei%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%A6%20should%20it%20be%20achieved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewoksoflife.com%2Fchinese-chicken-broccoli-brown-sauce%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EChinese%20takeout-style%20chicken%20with%20broccoli%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20in%20a%20brown%20sauce%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eshowed%20us%3A%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EHow%20effectively%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewoksoflife.com%2Fhow-to-velvet-chicken-stir-fry%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evelveted%20chicken%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20achieve%20browning%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHow%20tender%20the%20chicken%20would%20remain%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIf%20dry%20vegetables%20could%20achieve%20%3Cem%3Ewok%20hei%3C%2Fem%3E-like%20char%20in%20this%20pan%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIf%20bulky%20vegetables%20could%20resist%20steaming%20in%20a%20crowded%20pan%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAny%20hot%20spots%20or%20inconsistencies%20in%20heat%20dispersion%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHow%20fast%20and%20evenly%20sauces%20would%20reduce%20and%20thicken%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHow%20easy%20it%20was%20to%20coat%20ingredients%20in%20the%20sauce%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEase%20of%20handling%20and%20cleanup%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cp%3EI%20tried%20to%20use%20the%20same%20heat%20setting%20for%20each%20wok%2C%20but%20differing%20heat%20retention%20levels%20forced%20adaptation%20to%20avoid%20ruining%20the%20dish.%20I%20also%20used%20more%20oil%20for%20stainless%20steel%20woks%20to%20avoid%20sticking%2C%20and%20added%20broth%20to%20the%20fried%20rice%20in%20some%20instances%20since%20some%20materials%20were%20more%20apt%20to%20burn%20than%20char%20and%20required%20more%20moisture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESteak%20summer%20fried%20rice%2C%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Einspired%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmoguchinese.com%2Fmenu%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EM%C3%93G%C5%AA's%20Bang%20Bang%20Rice%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20a%20good%20demonstration%20of%3A%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EHow%20well%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewoksoflife.com%2Fprepare-beef-for-stir-fry%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evelveted%20red%20meat%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20sear%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHow%20tender%20the%20steak%20would%20remain%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENonstick%20abilities%20when%20used%20for%20semi-dry%2C%20cold-start%20egg%20frying%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIf%20onions%20could%20char%20effectively%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIf%20juicy%20ingredients%20like%20tomatoes%20blistered%20on%20impact%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIf%20adding%20wet%20leafy%20greens%20like%20baby%20Shanghai%20bok%20choy%20would%20result%20in%20steaming%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEase%20of%20transferring%20small%20pieces%20of%20food%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEase%20of%20handling%20and%20cleanup%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20science%20of%20wok%20cooking%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chicken%20and%20broccoli%20in%20a%20pan%20cooking%20as%20part%20of%20testing.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F60bfb3942feb6f00181ed9d0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENo%20matter%20which%20wok%20you%20pick%2C%20you'll%20have%20to%20take%20time%20to%20get%20to%20know%20it.%3Cp%3ESu-Jit%20Lin%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECooking%20in%20any%20of%20the%20best%20woks%20is%20an%20art%20and%20a%20science.%20The%20speed%20of%20execution%20and%20drama%20of%20it%20speaks%20to%20artistry%2C%20but%20the%20results%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmoguchinese.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EM%C3%93G%C5%AA%20Modern%20Chinese%20Kitchen%3C%2Fa%3E%20founder%20Mike%20Wang%2C%20developer%20of%20his%20restaurant's%20self-cooking%20robo-woks%20with%20his%20GenX%20Robotics%20division%2C%20puts%20it%2C%20%26quot%3Bhas%20everything%20to%20do%20with%20the%20mathematics%20of%20particle%20movement.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20science%20of%20woking%20is%20broken%20down%20to%20temperature%20control%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explains%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhich%20is%20done%20by%20elevating%20the%20wok%20with%20the%20hand%2C%20controlling%20the%20gas%20lever%20with%20one's%20leg%20during%20cooking%2C%20and%20flipping%20the%20ingredients%20inside%20the%20wok.%20At%20GenX%20Robotics%20and%20M%C3%93G%C5%AA%2C%20we%20studied%20the%20science%20of%20woking%20by%20using%20computer%20vision%20to%20track%20the%20movements%20of%20individual%20particles%20and%20how%20they%20move%20with%20the%20different%20viscosities%20of%20sauce.%20We%20investigated%20how%20those%20ingredients%20interacted%20with%20the%20surface%20of%20the%20cooking%20pan%2C%20the%20sauce%2C%20and%20other%20food%20particles.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20he%20and%20his%20team%20found%20was%20that%20the%20slightest%20variation%20could%20lead%20to%20notably%20different%20outcomes%2C%20which%20our%20own%20testing%20confirms%20on%20a%20broader%20scale.%20The%20takeaway%3A%20be%20patient%20as%20you%20learn%20the%20ins%20and%20outs%20of%20your%20wok.%20A%20learning%20curve%20is%20to%20be%20expected%20at%20first%2C%20but%20you'll%20soon%20be%20able%20to%20produce%20consistent%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EPro%20tip%3A%20temper%20your%20expectations%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20matter%20what%20wok%20you%20get%2C%20though%2C%20just%20know%20that%20results%20on%20an%20electric%20stove%20will%20be%20considerably%20less%20favorable%20than%20on%20a%20gas%20stove.%20And%20that%20same%20gas%20stove%20will%20fall%20well%20shy%20of%20what%20a%20commercial%20restaurant%20wok%20burner%20can%20produce.%20If%20you're%20looking%20to%20recreate%20a%20dish%20you%20had%20at%20a%20restaurant%2C%20be%20prepared%20for%20at%20least%20slightly%20different%20results%2C%20especially%20if%20you're%20working%20on%20an%20electric%20stove.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20home%20stove%20will%20be%20as%20immediately%20responsive%2C%20either.%20The%20instantaneousness%20of%20being%20able%20to%20crank%20up%20the%20heat%20and%20adjust%20it%20fast%20is%20a%20huge%20part%20of%20wok%20cooking.%20While%20certain%20materials%20help%20with%20heat%20distribution%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20consider%20the%20thickness%2C%20flexibility%2C%20flat%20surface%20area%2C%20and%20curvature%20of%20the%20wok%2C%20too.%20All%20of%20these%20contribute%20to%20its%20quality%20and%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20you%20get%20started%20cooking%20with%20the%20best%20wok%2C%20it'll%20be%20a%20matter%20of%20time%20until%20you%20master%20it%20%E2%80%A6%20and%20with%20that%2C%20fall%20in%20love%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETo%20get%20the%20most%20out%20of%20your%20wok%3A%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EStart%20with%20a%20great%20wok%20(like%20one%20of%20our%20picks)%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUse%20a%20gas%20stove%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUse%20the%20most%20powerful%20burner%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETurn%20up%20the%20heat%20so%20the%20flames%20come%20up%20the%20side%20of%20the%20wok%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EControl%20temperature%20by%20lifting%20the%20wok%20off%20the%20burner%20and%20moving%20items%20that%20are%20cooking%20too%20fast%20to%20the%20walls%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EExpect%20a%20learning%20curve%20as%20you%20figure%20out%20the%20intricacies%20of%20your%20wok%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWok%20FAQs%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chicken%20and%20broccoli%20prepared%20in%20a%20wok%20as%20part%20of%20testing.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F60bfc4fd2feb6f00181eda28%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222274%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20curvature%20of%20the%20best%20woks%20facilitates%20two%20types%20of%20cooking%3A%20tumble%20and%20toss.%3Cp%3ESu-Jit%20Lin%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch3%3EIs%20it%20better%20to%20get%20a%20more%20or%20less%20curved%20wok%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20high%20curvature%20results%20in%20a%20broader%20base%20for%20maximum%20area%20of%20heat%20transfer%2C%26quot%3B%20Wang%20says.%20That%20means%20one%20with%20a%20greater%20curve%20and%20higher%20walls%20means%20heat%20is%20less%20concentrated%20on%20the%20flat%20bottom%20and%20better%20distributed%20up%20the%20walls.%20However%2C%20an%20overly%20steep%20wok%20can%20trap%20steam%20and%20make%20your%20food%20get%20limp%20and%20soggy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20flatter%2C%20lower%20wok%20has%20disadvantages%20of%20its%20own.%20You%20simply%20can't%20mix%20well%20with%20a%20broad%20wok%20floor%2C%20and%20you%20definitely%20can't%20toss.%20And%20while%20tumbling%20(as%20opposed%20to%20stirring)%20is%20the%20right%20way%20to%20work%20food%20in%20a%20wok%2C%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20throw%20ingredients%20out%20of%20it.%20Curved%20walls%20help%20cue%20flipping%20your%20ingredients%20back%20into%20the%20pan%2C%20and%20taller%20sides%20keep%20errant%20pieces%20from%20escaping.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bottom%20line%20is%20that%20proportion%20is%20critical%20to%20creating%20the%20varying%20heat%20zones%20needed%2C%20since%20stir-fry%20components%20usually%20cook%20and%20brown%20at%20different%20rates.%20Even%20layering%20your%20ingredients%20can't%20save%20you%20from%20over-%20or%20undercooking%20if%20the%20temperature%20is%20too%20uniform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat's%20the%20best%20way%20to%20season%20a%20wok%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EUnless%20you're%20getting%20a%20carbon%20steel%20wok%20(which%20we%20did%20not%20test)%2C%20you%20would%20season%20a%20wok%20the%20way%20you%20would%20any%20pan%20of%20the%20same%20material.%20However%2C%20most%20nonstick%20woks%20are%20ready%20to%20go%20right%20out%20of%20the%20box.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20detailed%20instructions%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fhow-to-season-cast-iron%5C%22%3Ehow%20to%20season%20cast%20iron%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewoks%20will%20help%20you%C2%A0get%20that%20material%20prepped%20for%20duty.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20%3Cem%3Edo%20%3C%2Fem%3Edecide%20to%20go%20rogue%20off%20our%20recommendations%20and%20opt%20for%20traditional%20carbon%20steel%2C%20Wang%20emphasizes%20the%20importance%20of%20prepping%20it%20properly.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20systematic%20process%20where%20the%20wok%20adapts%20a%20nonstick%20nature%20that%20comes%20with%20repeated%20oil%20washing%2C%26quot%3B%20developing%20a%20blackened%20patina%20from%20oil%20that's%20seared%20on%20in%20a%20hard%20coat%2C%20like%20with%20cast%20iron.%20However%2C%20this%20takes%20a%20lot%20of%20use%20and%20tremendous%20heat%20exposure%20to%20develop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20tools%20do%20I%20need%20to%20cook%20with%20a%20wok%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20sponsored%20nofollow%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiipgf_122717_best-woks-20%26h%3D7c80330161e7003222fdace5b16e7c8c14ad6ade4ac3bff851590d143ffca07e%26postID%3D61b8efc7f2a36b1ac9f41dee%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fkitchen%252Fbest-wok%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252Fgp%252Fproduct%252FB084JLM61C%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echuan%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20may%20look%20like%20a%20spatula%20at%20first%20glance%2C%20but%20there's%20a%20curvature%20that%20distinguishes%20it.%20Wok%20turners%20are%20angled%20differently%2C%20and%20where%20the%20head%20connects%20to%20the%20handle%2C%20you'll%20notice%20a%20slight%20rounding%20that's%20designed%20to%20seamlessly%20follow%20the%20soft%20angles%20of%20a%20wok.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20usually%20have%20raised%20side%20edges%20that%20center%20your%20scoop%20as%20you%20tumble-cook%20or%20serve.%20This%20supports%20the%20tossing%20and%20mixing%20motion%20required%20for%20stir-frying%20while%20a%20regular%20flat%20spatula%20is%20more%20for%20shifting%20ingredients.%20The%20best%20ones%20have%20a%20very%20thin%20front%20edge%20that%20gets%20under%20your%20food%20better%20that%20has%20a%20soft%20arc%20that%20lets%20it%20reach%20into%20a%20round%20bottom%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat's%20the%20difference%20between%20a%20wok%20and%20a%20frying%20pan%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20construction%2C%20woks%20and%20frying%20pans%20are%20like%20distant%20cookware%20cousins.%20A%20frying%20pan%20has%20short%2C%20slightly%20angled%20walls%20and%20a%20wide%2C%20flat%20bottom.%20While%20you%20can%20make%20a%20stir%20fry%20in%20a%20frying%20pan%2C%20you%20will%20not%20get%20the%20same%20results%20as%20you%20do%20in%20a%20wok%20because%20there%20isn't%20as%20much%20temperature%20variation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECooking%20in%20a%20wok%20relies%20on%20regular%20movement%20of%20the%20i